@ConditionalOnProperty Annotations:
Beans is created conditionally(Mean bean can be created or not).

@ConditionalOnProperty is used to enable or disable a bean/configuration based on a value in the application.properties / application.yml file.
ðŸ‘‰ Very useful when:
You want feature on/off
Different behavior for dev / test / prod
Avoid loading unnecessary beans

Advantage:
Toggling of feature(In Application.property we can add if we want to create bean for the particular class)
Avoid cluttering App context with un-necessary beans
Save memory
Reduce app Startup time

Disadvantages:
Misconfiguration can happen
Code complexity when over used.
Multiple bean creation with same config, brings confusion.
Complexity in managing

